  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison thanks Samuel May, Jr., for obtaining a passage homeward for George Thompson. The suffrage question is now obsolete in the South. Garrison believes that &quot;the enfranchised freedmen, under the Congressional reconstruction act, will never allow themselves to be deprived of the ballot, ...&quot; Mr. and Mrs. Oliver Johnson are now visiting at William Lloyd Garrison&apos;s home.</subfield>
